eNCA took to the streets of Joburg and spoke to people to find out their response to President Cyril Ramaphosa's address of the nation last night. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - In President Cyril Ramaphosa's address of the nation on Tuesday night, he eased several restrictions. The wearing of masks is no longer required outdoors, indoor and outdoor venues can be packed to 50-percent of their capacity and social distancing is down to one metre. WATCH | Masks no longer required when outdoors in SA eNCA took to the streets of Joburg and spoke to people to find out their response to Tuesday night’s address. 